translations:
‘He
			brought out his she-horse, his filly, from behind the houses, put
			a saddle on her back and bridled her well’ 78/88;

‘She
			squeezed in behind him and clasped him to her breast’ LuF
			276/11;

‘He
			looked around and saw a girl who was clasping (him) to her breast’
			LuF 278/13;
